-- Arkema Raises 2010 Profit Target as Industrial Chemicals Demand Increases
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-11-09T06:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/arkema-raises-2010-profit-target-as-industrial-chemicals-demand-increases.html
Arkema SA raised its profit target
for 2010 as demand for industrial chemicals increased.  Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and
amortization will reach about 740 million euros this year, the
company said in an emailed statement. Arkema had forecast profit
on that measure would exceed 600 million euros.  Third-quarter net income of 130 million euros compared with
a year-earlier loss of 3 million euros, the company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  